{{Use Australian English|date=November 2016}} {{ Infobox V8 Supercar race report | flag = Queensland | title = 2017 Watpac Townsville 400 | round_no = 7 | season_no = 14 | year = 2017 | series = IVSC | track_map = Townsville (Australia) street circuit track map.svg | date = 7–9 July | location = [[Townsville]], [[Queensland]] | circuit = Townsville Street Circuit | weather = | race1_laps = 70 | race1_dist = 200 | pole1 = {{flagicon|NZL}} [[Scott McLaughlin (racing driver)|Scott McLaughlin]] | pole1_team = [[DJR Team Penske]] | pole1_time = 1:12.0730 | winner1 = {{flagicon|NZL}} [[Scott McLaughlin (racing driver)|Scott McLaughlin]] | winner1_team = [[DJR Team Penske]] | winner1_time = 1:28:19.7418 | race2_laps = 70 | race2_dist = 200 | pole2 = {{flagicon|NZL}} [[Scott McLaughlin (racing driver)|Scott McLaughlin]] | pole2_team = [[DJR Team Penske]] | pole2_time = 1:11.9907 | winner2 = {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Jamie Whincup]] | winner2_team = [[Triple Eight Race Engineering]] | winner2_time = 1:28:12.5243 }}
The '''2017 Watpac Townsville 400''' was an [[auto racing|motor racing]] event for the [[Supercars Championship]], held on the weekend of 7 to 9 July 2017. The event was held at [[Townsville Street Circuit]] near [[Townsville]], [[Queensland]] and consisted of two races, both 200 kilometres in length. It is the seventh event of fourteen in the [[2017 Supercars Championship]] and hosted Races 13 and 14 of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.supercars.com/2017-watpac-townsville-400-schedule-results/|title=2017 Watpac Townsville 400 Schedule & Results |website=Supercars.com|accessdate=11 December 2017}}</ref>
==Background== ===Driver changes=== [[Aaren Russell]] was drafted in to replace [[Cameron McConville]] at [[Lucas Dumbrell Motorsport]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.speedcafe.com/2017/07/06/aaren-russell-pilot-ldm-commodore/|title=Aaren Russell to pilot LDM Commodore - Speedcafe|website=Speedcafe.com|accessdate=11 December 2017}}</ref>
